# .dev.vars.example

# This file shows which environment variables are needed for local development.
# Copy this to .dev.vars and fill in your actual values.
# NEVER commit .dev.vars to git (it's in .gitignore)

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DATABASE CONNECTION (Required)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Get this from Neon console: https://console.neon.tech
# Format: postgres://[user]:[password]@[host]/[database]
# Example: postgres://neondb_owner:abc123@ep-cool-db-123.us-east-1.neon.tech/neondb
NEON_URL=postgres://

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AUTHENTICATION (Required)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Generate a random 32-byte secret for local development (just for local testing):
# macOS/Linux:   openssl rand -base64 32
# Windows PowerShell: [Convert]::ToBase64String([byte[]]$(1..32|%{Get-Random -Maximum 256}))
# Minimum 32 characters, recommend base64url
JWT_SECRET=your-random-32-byte-secret-here

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ERROR TRACKING (Required for local testing, but optional field)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Get from Sentry: https://sentry.io/organizations/your-org/projects/
# Format: https://[key]@[host]/[project-id]
# Example: https://abc123def456@o123.ingest.sentry.io/4567890
SENTRY_DSN=https://

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ANALYTICS (Required for local testing, but optional field)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Get from PostHog: https://app.posthog.com/settings/project/keys
# Format: phc_[hex chars]
# Example: phc_abc123def456abc123def456
POSTHOG_KEY=phc_

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOTES
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# In production, these come from:
#   - Bindings (DB, AUTH_RATE_LIMITER): wrangler.jsonc
#   - Secrets (JWT_SECRET, SENTRY_DSN, POSTHOG_KEY): GitHub Actions environment secrets
#   - Non-secret vars (ENVIRONMENT, WORKER_NAME): wrangler.jsonc [vars] section
#
# For local development, use this .dev.vars file.
# Wrangler reads .dev.vars automatically when running `npm run dev`.
#
# If you see TypeScript errors about missing env vars, check:
#   1. Is .dev.vars file present?
#   2. Does .dev.vars have all required fields from src/env.ts?
#   3. Are the values valid (not empty strings)?
#
# For help, see: docs/runbooks/environment-isolation-and-verification.md
